cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on developing a visual object classifier driven by human brain signals, which involves the use of EEG data and deep learning techniques such as RNN and CNN. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

Additionally, the paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The study also involves human subjects and their brain activity, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). 

The use of deep learning techniques for classification and generalization could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
